    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_22374627" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/22374627" />
    <a title="Timothy Juhl" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1060129-timothy-juhl"><img alt="Timothy Juhl" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1593870675p2/1060129.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/22374627?book_show_action=true">May 16, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Timothy Juhl" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Timothy Juhl" href="/user/show/1060129-timothy-juhl">Timothy Juhl</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780394545370" href="/book/show/1100994.Oldest_Living_Confederate_Widow_Tells_All">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Southern bookclubs and anyone looking for great literature.</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1060129-timothy-juhl?shelf=gay-author">gay-author</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer22374627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7305638503594099264">Officially, what I consider a tome, Gurganus&apos; masterpiece, is one of the finest examples of historical fiction, and particularly the Civil War.<br/><br/>Forget the dreadful made-for-television movie, forget &apos;<a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18405.Gone_With_The_Wind' title='Gone With The Wind by Margaret Mitchell' rel='nofollow noopener'>Gone With The Wind</a>&apos;. There is a langorous chapter midway into the story that depicts Sherman&apos;s March to the sea, told by the plantation owners and slaves who watched the plumes of smoke from distant homes, knowing their lives would be burned out from under them very soon. The images evoked in this cha</span>
  <span id="freeText7305638503594099264" style="display:none">Officially, what I consider a tome, Gurganus' masterpiece, is one of the finest examples of historical fiction, and particularly the Civil War.<br /><br />Forget the dreadful made-for-television movie, forget '<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18405.Gone_With_The_Wind" title="Gone With The Wind by Margaret Mitchell" rel="nofollow noopener">Gone With The Wind</a>'. There is a langorous chapter midway into the story that depicts Sherman's March to the sea, told by the plantation owners and slaves who watched the plumes of smoke from distant homes, knowing their lives would be burned out from under them very soon. The images evoked in this chapter still resonate with me.<br /><br />I've been a fan of Mr. Gurganus ever since.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7305638503594099264" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


